```typescript
function ({value}, {result}, {state, onCleanup}) {
  const timer = state.get("timer");
  if (timer) {
    clearTimeout(timer);
  }
  const newTimer = setTimeout(() => {
    result.next(value);
  }, 500);

  state.set("timer", newTimer);
  onCleanup(() => clearTimeout(timer));
}
```
This debounce node will wait for 500ms after receiving a value before emitting it. If a new value is received before the 500ms are up, the timer is reset and the debounce starts again.
